TellFriends: 1.  Ultimately, Company's showed their established support for customers by (more than) replacing the broken dishes which were in the original shipment.  Additionally, in the end, they did not charge us the amounts which appeared on the online orders related to the replacements.  2.  However, it was disheartening and frustrating to have so many broken pieces in the original shipment.  The breakage was clearly the result of the manufacturer using too small a box and having totally inadequate padding to protect the dishes.  Thus, that was not Company's fault.  In the instance of these settings, where one broken piece cannot be replaced except with an entire new SETTING, it would likely behoove Company's to either stop ordering from this manufacturer, or insist they change their packaging to properly protect the dishes, or re-pack them. We received 12 place settings for the price of 8 at a sale price! That doesn't sound like good business to me!  And don't include price on replacement orders!
AdditionalFeedback: It was frustrating as explained earlier but ultimately, Company's went "above and beyond" and the gift of dishes ended up as 12 settings (four of the five broken pieces can be glued, less than perfect, but usable) versus the 8 which were ordered.  Though it took many calls and many hours to clarify that the charges shown on the replacement orders were not being charged to my account, in the end all replacements were free, but it took too long and too many efforts (one of them a 45 minute phone call!) to give me the assurance that I would not be charged for replacing the broken pieces.
